  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reinforcing STI systems, indigenous peoples and local communities in the Andean subregion</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The work with STI systems, indigenous peoples and local communities will be continued in 2018-2019. According to the conclusion of different first-order subregional stakeholders, including S&amp;T institutions of central governments in Bolivia, Ecuador, Peru and Venezuela, the dialogue among different forms of knowledge (di&#xE1;logo de saberes) will be prioritized in the Andean subregion.
Conventional STI systems in the Member States of the Andean subregion will be supported and strengthened and at the same time the dialogue with indigenous knowledge systems will be promoted.
On-going interdisciplinary processes in the region with a strong Andean component including the Spiritual Reserves of Humanity and the Open Initiative on Mangroves and Sustainable Development will be promoted.</narrative>
  </description>
